An introduction to main issues in the philosophy of mind, including the main approaches to the mind-body problem, consciousness, artificial intelligence, thought and language, etc.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The main general objective is to familiarize students with an important branch of the contemporary analytical philosophical tradition. The course will give an overview of the main concepts, topics and arguments in philosophy of mind, develop the skill of reading philosophy texts and the philosophical writing skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course the students should: 1) master the most important concepts in philosophy of mind, 2) know the main metaphysical positions in philosophy of mind, 3) be able to read, understand and discuss texts on philosophy of mind, 4) be competent in philosophical problem-setting and able to find relevant literature, 5) know and apply the basics of philosophical essay writing.
